{"id":14881819,"mediaExerciseId":"59c29c8a-a350-4106-be1a-10d6c4869cd5","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612487,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":786,"solutions":[{"id":5997308,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will tackle the differences between a futures contract and a forward contract. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The main difference between a futures and a forward contract is that in the futures contract, the gains and losses are taken into account **each day of the contract**. On the other hand, a forward contract only takes into account the gains/losses **at the end of the contract**. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/00a0f97364b05a15fee13c1f67fe58e3/a58e11f089d730b04070da9d794c6a1c/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":73,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/00a0f97364b05a15fee13c1f67fe58e3/a58e11f089d730b04070da9d794c6a1c/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The reason why futures are much more common is because it is standardized and monitored. A forward contract may be difficult since there are no institutions involved in the mediation of this contracts. This is also why a forward contract may be preferred by two parties that want to have more complex terms since the forward contract is fully custom. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":179,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/00a0f97364b05a15fee13c1f67fe58e3/f6987440386d88655c364a1885ddcd9d/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/00a0f97364b05a15fee13c1f67fe58e3/f6987440386d88655c364a1885ddcd9d/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"42ba0221-0e17-428d-8d6e-0140db4629dc","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881820,"exerciseName":"4","page":786,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"45e09b0b-ef60-4b2a-b673-040bf7b1b0cb","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-critical-thinking-questions-4-45e09b0b-ef60-4b2a-b673-040bf7b1b0cb"},{"id":14881821,"exerciseName":"5","page":786,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"fe8c21e3-fe12-47c2-b426-72a91e007a70","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-critical-thinking-questions-5-fe8c21e3-fe12-47c2-b426-72a91e007a70"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881818,"exerciseName":"2","page":786,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"45152a5b-6340-41e4-938e-d0cf9490f9a5","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-critical-thinking-questions-2-45152a5b-63